This article is a press gaggle by Jay Carney, the White House Press Secretary, on June 24, 2011. Carney discusses the upcoming meetings between President Obama and the Senate Majority Leader and Senate Minority Leader, as well as the progress made in deficit reduction talks. He emphasizes the President's commitment to a balanced approach to deficit reduction, where the burden is not solely placed on the middle class and seniors. Carney also addresses questions about the President's meetings with Speaker Boehner and his stance on tax cuts. Additionally, he mentions the House vote on Libya and expresses disappointment with the result. Carney concludes by providing a brief overview of the President's schedule for the week ahead, including meetings with congressional leaders, events honoring sports teams, and a farewell ceremony for Secretary of Defense Robert Gates.